{
  "document": {
    "type": "document",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "Theorem",
        "label": "metric.root.theorem",
        "header": "Theorem",
        "claim": "Let $(X,d)$ be a metric space, and let $x,y \\in X$ be distinct points with $d(x,y)=\\epsilon>0$. Then the open balls $B(x,\\epsilon/3)$ and $B(y,\\epsilon/3)$ are disjoint.",
        "proof": {
          "type": "contradiction_statement",
          "assumption": "B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)≠∅",
          "proof": {
            "type": "Proof",
            "proof_steps": [
              {
                "type": "Proof",
                "claim_label": "B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)≠∅",
                "proof_steps": [
                  {
                    "type": "Proof",
                    "claim_label": "∃z∈X, z∈B(x,ε/3) ∧ z∈B(y,ε/3)",
                    "proof_steps": [
                      {
                        "type": "Proof",
                        "claim_label": "∃z∈X, z∈B(x,ε/3) ∧ z∈B(y,ε/3)",
                        "proof_steps": [
                          {
                            "type": "Proof",
                            "claim_label": "z∈B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)",
                            "proof_steps": [
                              {
                                "type": "Proof",
                                "claim_label": "z∈B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)",
                                "proof_steps": [
                                  {
                                    "type": "let_statement",
                                    "variable_name": "z",
                                    "variable_type": "element of B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)",
                                    "statement": "Choose z∈B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)."
                                  },
                                  {
                                    "type": "assert_statement",
                                    "claim": "z∈B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)",
                                    "proof_method": "by the choice of z from the nonempty intersection"
                                  }
                                ],
                                "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption.witness.choose_z.witness_choice.choice",
                                "status": "resolved",
                                "text": "Since B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)≠∅, choose z∈B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)."
                              }
                            ],
                            "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption.witness.choose_z.witness_choice",
                            "status": "resolved"
                          },
                          {
                            "type": "assert_statement",
                            "claim": "z∈B(x,ε/3) ∧ z∈B(y,ε/3)",
                            "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption.witness.choose_z.membership_verification",
                            "status": "classified",
                            "text": "Because z lies in the intersection, z∈B(x,ε/3) and z∈B(y,ε/3)."
                          }
                        ],
                        "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption.witness.choose_z",
                        "status": "decomposed"
                      },
                      {
                        "type": "assert_statement",
                        "claim": "z∈B(x,ε/3) ∧ z∈B(y,ε/3)",
                        "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption.witness.membership",
                        "status": "classified",
                        "text": "Membership z∈B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3) gives z∈B(x,ε/3) and z∈B(y,ε/3)."
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption.witness",
                    "status": "decomposed"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.assumption",
                "status": "decomposed"
              },
              {
                "type": "calculation_to_contradiction",
                "start": "z∈B(x,ε/3)",
                "target": "contradiction",
                "goal_relation": "mixed",
                "steps": [
                  {
                    "from": "z∈B(x,ε/3)",
                    "relation": "->",
                    "to": "d(z,x)<ε/3",
                    "justification": "Definition of open ball"
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "z∈B(y,ε/3)",
                    "relation": "->",
                    "to": "d(z,y)<ε/3",
                    "justification": "Definition of open ball"
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "d(x,y)",
                    "relation": "<=",
                    "to": "d(x,z)+d(z,y)",
                    "justification": "Triangle inequality, using symmetry d(x,z)=d(z,x)",
                    "side_conditions": [
                      "d is a metric"
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "d(x,z)+d(z,y)",
                    "relation": "<",
                    "to": "ε/3+ε/3",
                    "justification": "From d(z,x)<ε/3 and d(z,y)<ε/3, using symmetry d(x,z)=d(z,x)"
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "ε/3+ε/3",
                    "relation": "=",
                    "to": "2ε/3",
                    "justification": "Arithmetic simplification"
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "d(x,y)",
                    "relation": "<",
                    "to": "2ε/3",
                    "justification": "Combining the preceding inequalities"
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "ε",
                    "relation": "<",
                    "to": "2ε/3",
                    "justification": "Substitute d(x,y)=ε"
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "ε<2ε/3 and ε>0",
                    "relation": "->",
                    "to": "1<2/3",
                    "justification": "Divide the inequality ε<2ε/3 by the positive quantity ε",
                    "side_conditions": [
                      "ε>0"
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "from": "1<2/3",
                    "relation": "->",
                    "to": "contradiction",
                    "justification": "Arithmetic impossibility"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.contradiction",
                "status": "resolved",
                "text": "From z∈B(x,ε/3) and z∈B(y,ε/3), we have d(z,x)<ε/3 and d(z,y)<ε/3. By the triangle inequality, d(x,y)≤d(x,z)+d(z,y)<ε/3+ε/3=2ε/3. Since d(x,y)=ε, this gives ε<2ε/3, and because ε>0, 1<2/3, a contradiction."
              },
              {
                "type": "Proof",
                "claim_label": "B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)=∅",
                "proof_steps": [
                  {
                    "type": "assert_statement",
                    "claim": "B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)=∅",
                    "proof_method": "Since assuming that a point lies in B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3) leads to a contradiction, no such point exists."
                  }
                ],
                "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root.conclusion",
                "status": "resolved",
                "text": "This contradiction arises from the assumption that a point lies in the intersection. Therefore no such point exists, so B(x,ε/3)∩B(y,ε/3)=∅."
              }
            ]
          },
          "id": "metric.root.theorem.proof.root",
          "status": "decomposed"
        },
        "id": "metric.root.theorem",
        "status": "decomposed"
      }
    ]
  }
}
